This paper is primarily focused on addressing the mode collapse problem in GANs, which is a common issue in the field of deep learning and specifically in the subfield of generative models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) as GANs are often used for image generation. Additionally, the paper involves theoretical analysis and regularization techniques, which are also relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also includes some graph-based analysis, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of cs.GR (Computer Science and Game Theory).
